ne; max-height: 0px; overflow: hidden; mso-hide:all;">Welcome back to Wall =
Power. I=E2=80=99m Marion Maneker. It=E2=80=99s a fine Sunday evening in wi=
ntertime. Come sit by the fire and let=E2=80=99s talk about the art world. =
Larry Gagosian built his global empire of galleries by launching each new s=
pace with a show featuring Cy Twombly. The pattern began in 1989 when Twomb=
ly opened Gagosian=E2=80=99s 980 Madison Avenue flagship gallery with an ex=
hibition of his legendary Bolsena paintings. The partnership was mutually b=
eneficial: Gagosian burnished his prestige with shows by one of the most re=
vered artists of his time; meanwhile, Twombly got a constant goad to push h=
imself late in his career=E2=80=94a time when many artists are content to r=
est on their fame.</div>
