e move. Galleries like Nahmad Contemporary, White Cube, Robilant+Voena, Ven=
us Over Manhattan, Edward Tyler Nahem, Dickinson, and others have all eithe=
r had offices there recently, or are still there. I=E2=80=99ve spoken to at=
 least two of the other gallery tenants=E2=80=94much smaller players=E2=80=
=94who are sanguine about moving on, and are unlikely to move into a simila=
r retail space. Such is the changing nature of art dealing, and the loss of=
 decent
real estate options on the Upper East Side.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">When Gagosi=
an opened the galley in 1989, he was able to show <strong>Cy Twombly</stron=
g>=E2=80=99s <em>Bolsena</em> paintings, made 20 years earlier and provoked=
 by the Apollo missions to the moon. After that, as Gagosian pioneered the =
concept of a single art gallery with globe-girdling outposts, he would cont=
inue to call on Twombly to inaugurate his new gallery spaces.
=E2=80=9CFor 10 years,=E2=80=9D the artist <strong>Jenny Saville</strong>, =
also a star of Gagosian=E2=80=99s stable, said in her lecture at the Menil =
Collection a year ago, =E2=80=9Cthere was a challenge of sorts going on bet=
ween Twombly and Larry Gagosian.=E2=80=9D As Saville described it, this gam=
e of one-upsmanship=E2=80=94<em>What would you create for this space, Cy?</=
em> <em>What about this one?=E2=80=94</em>produced an extraordinary and une=
xpected body of work by the aging artist. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m not sure Two=
mbly would have created this run of paintings
without those spaces and that encouragement,=E2=80=9D she said. =E2=80=9CAn=
d that he agreed to participate with this level of energy, at this moment i=
n his life, made Gagosian the gallery it is today.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"=
margin:0;"><br/>Now, as a fitting coda for the gallery=E2=80=94a way to loo=
k back and underline what was most important=E2=80=94Gagosian has chosen to=
 mount a show simply titled <em>Cy Twombly</em>, featuring four key bodies =
of work mostly borrowed from private collections and Twombly=E2=80=99s fami=
ly, some of which have
never been seen before.</p></div>
